Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling customer support at Viagra.

Speaker 2: My name is Jessie.

Speaker 1: I'm sorry, you said your last name was Warner?

Speaker 2: No, Borchardt.

Speaker 1: B-O-R-C-H-A-R-D-T.

Speaker 1: I found you here.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much, Mr. Borchardt.

Speaker 1: And I have you at 946 Crossing Wayne Delano, Minnesota?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Close enough to the pronunciation.

Speaker 2: Delano?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: What can I help you with?

Speaker 2: I need to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: I've used the item twice now, and it has had absolutely no effect other than normal.

Speaker 2: So far, I've tried Blue True, Rose Sparks, you guys were new, so I gave you a shot, nothing.

Speaker 1: Nothing?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Let me check something if you don't mind, because we don't get complaints about the—

Speaker 2: stone plaque I've gotten.

Speaker 1: Do you have the pills there with you by any chance?

Speaker 2: I want to double check something.

Speaker 1: If you don't mind, I'll be super quick.

Speaker 2: Not handy, no.

Speaker 1: Not handy?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Let me double check something here, then I'll check with the pharmacy and see what happened—

Speaker 2: here.

Speaker 1: I've literally had three guys just reorder within two weeks, because it's so strong.

Speaker 2: Hold on.

Speaker 1: So to me, that doesn't make any sense.

Speaker 2: Let me double check and make sure.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: It looks like you've got the American-made one.

Speaker 1: I can do this for you.

Speaker 2: I'm happy to replace it with the French ones, because the French ones are the ones that—

Speaker 1: everyone calls about, and I'll just replace them for you at no cost to you, clearly.

Speaker 2: We'd like for you to try the French ones.

Speaker 1: Those are the ones that are super fast, and I can get that out to you with priority.

Speaker 2: Make sure you don't get charged for anything else, and we'll hold everything for 60 days—

Speaker 1: for you, so that way you can just try them and let us know if it's a fit for you or not.

Speaker 2: So what's the difference between the two products?

Speaker 1: It's a pretty gigantic difference, because the one that's from France is the one that's—

Speaker 2: made at the Pfizer facility, so that's the one that's longest-lasting, super quick, the—

Speaker 1: one that people call us about, and the one that they keep reordering, so that one's in—

Speaker 2: high demand.

Speaker 1: So then why did I get the other one and pay express mailing for that, if it's not...

Speaker 2: It looks like you ordered this online.

Speaker 1: I don't know if you...

Speaker 2: I don't know.

Speaker 1: I don't know if you accidentally selected the wrong one or whatnot, but I'm happy to—

Speaker 2: replace it for you, and we'll send it out with priority.

Speaker 1: But yeah, I'm not going to charge you for this.

Speaker 2: We'd rather you try it and see how you like it before doing anything else.

Speaker 1: And what...

Speaker 2: How many milligrams?

Speaker 1: Same thing.

Speaker 2: Exact same thing, except this one is the one from France, so it's 100 milligrams.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: We'll give it one more shot.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Very good.

Speaker 1: We'll get this out to you in the mail, okay?

Speaker 2: And then everything is paused for 60 days.

Speaker 1: Let us know.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you.
